<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="547" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="63.[1403,2611,3085,3482]" pageId="63" pageNumber="547">
In 1961, L. de la Torre considered 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Shamel" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[1914,2073,3164,3197]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Sturnira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="547" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bogotensis">S. bogotensis</taxonomicName>
a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tshudi" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[2310,2479,3164,3197]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Sturnira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="547" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="erythromos">S. erythromos</taxonomicName>
but later treated it as a valid species. Cladistic analyses recovered them assister species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1404,2215,3282,3315]" pageId="63" pageNumber="547" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6458876" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6458876" box="[1404,2215,3282,3315]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6458876/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="547" startId="63.[1404,1576,3282,3315]" targetBox="[169,761,291,707]" targetPageId="64">
